                      Poets passion and philosophy                    The Asiatic Society presents a two-day seminar of UNESCO proposal on Maulana Rumi, the great Sufi thinker. To the Western world, his teachings are one of the best introductions to the philosophy and practice of Sufism. Rumi believed in the continuous progression of the soul through the process of life and death. The general theme of his philosophy is essentially the concept of Tawhid (union) and re-union with his Beloved. Rumis importance transcends national and ethnic borders. Persian literature in Iran, Afghanistan, Tajikistan and Pakistan sees him as its most significant classical poets and an influence on many poets through history including the likes of Iqbal and Kazi Nazrul Islam of India. The inaugural address will be delivered by Surabhi Banerjee followed by an introduction on the seminars theme by Osman Ghani.                  Event: A seminar on Sufi Poet Rumis poetry and philosophy When: January 28 amp; 29; 10.30 am Where: The Asiatic Society, Vidyasagar Hall	                    
